      <section>
        <title>How the “Celtic Tiger” did it? Tech-economy is the way!</title>
        <chapter>
          <paragraph>
            One of the main reason is that Ireland is widely known as a tax haven.
            Several prominent U.S. technological corporations have headquarters there,
            to save money on taxes. How they did it? Which company moved to Ireland?
            <list type="unordered">
              <item>Lots of companies are located in Dublin but they are supervised in
                US in this way they are considered “stateless corporations”.
                They don’t pay between 30% taxes in US but 12% in Ireland
              </item>
              <item>In order to be an Irish corporation you have to be registrated
                in Dublin and supervised in Ireland.
              </item>
              <item>On the other hand In order to be an United State corporation
                you have to be supervised in US
              </item>
            </list>
          </paragraph>
        </chapter>
